    "body": "### Problem\n\n  When using the minimal autocmd to automatically enter insert mode in a terminal buffer:  \n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('TermOpen', { command = 'startinsert' })\n```\n\nAnd then running a shell script via `:term ./%` (e.g., with the file `a.sh` containing `echo \"hello world\"`), the cursor position after the command finishes differs between Neovim 0.12.1 and previous versions.  \n\n\n0.10.4\n\n<img width=\"259\" height=\"104\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cc3fe220-4514-497c-a001-c1840ed5db8a\" />\n\n0.12.1\n\n<img width=\"228\" height=\"86\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d50134c8-26cf-4e0a-8a3c-d865d96a05d7\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean a.sh\n:lua vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('TermOpen', {  command = 'startinsert' })\n:term ./%\n\n`a.sh` containing `echo \"hello world\"`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nJust like before\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.46.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nsystem package manager",
